\section{Predictions and Experimental Testability}
1. Imperfect decoherence revivals scaling with engineered \(d_\text{web}\).
2. Born-rule wobbles (TVD \(\sim0.3\)--0.5) in multi-path interferometry.
3. Gravity-modulated coherence asymmetries in vertical cat states.
4. GOE level statistics in chaotic web lattices.

All effects are doubly-exponentially suppressed macroscopically.

\section{Relation to MWI, LQG, and String Theory}
ILW contains MWI as the \(\lambda\to0\) limit. It is compatible with LQG as an effective coarse-graining and with string theory via compact extra dimensions in the hybrid model.

\section{Conclusions}
ILW is a mathematically precise, numerically validated extension of quantum mechanics that adds one geometric postulate while remaining fully unitary and falsifiable. Future work includes higher-dimensional chaotic manifolds and full back-reaction.

